{subhead}New Amiga Staff{def}
{left}
{pp}
{bold}Frank Wilde elected Chairmain of Amiga{nobold}
{pp}
On 6th of December the Board of Directorys have elected Frank Wilde as their new
Chairman of the Board to help expand the Amiga business into new markets and new
products.
{pp}
Frank wilde was President and Chief Executive of Ravisent Technologies since April 1998.
He will bring eighteen years of sales, marketing and business development experience
from industries as IBM, Dell and Memorex Telex Corp.
{pp}
Ravisent main product was CinePlayer which played vartious video and audio media
on the PC, such as DVD, MPEG, Dolby Digital, Digital TV and HDTV.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Sanjay Menon - Vice President of Engineering{nobold}
{pp}
Mr Menon has been hired by Amiga to be Vice President of Engineering, responsilbe for
delivering Amiga solutions to various platforms.
{pp}
He will bring ten years of development an management experience to Amiga and is adept
at planning and executing development stategies in a timely fashion. Recently, he was
employed at Microsoft shipping portions of the Microsoft JVM with Internet Explorer.
Before that he was a Lead Developer at Connectsoft Corp in advanced communication
applications and protocols.
{pp}